<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Axiom_of_choice&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.apronus.com/provenmath/choice.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.apronus.com/provenmath/choice.htm" rel="nofollow">Axiom of Choice and Its Equivalents at ProvenMath</a> includes formal statement of the Axiom of Choice, Hausdorff's Maximal Principle, Zorn's Lemma and formal proofs of their equivalence down to the finest detail.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.math.purdue.edu/~jer/cgi-bin/conseq.html" class="external text" title="http://www.math.purdue.edu/~jer/cgi-bin/conseq.html" rel="nofollow">Consequences of the Axiom of Choice</a>, based on the book by <a href="http://www.emunix.emich.edu/~phoward/" class="external text" title="http://www.emunix.emich.edu/~phoward/" rel="nofollow">Paul Howard</a> and Jean Rubin.</li>
<li><a href="http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/axiom-choice" class="external text" title="http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/axiom-choice" rel="nofollow">The Axiom of Choice</a> entry in the <i><a href="/wiki/Stanford_Encyclopedia_of_Philosophy" title="Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy">Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy</a></i> by John L. Bell</li>
</ul>


